 The following two equations are the core of the UMS module in [29], where the controlling signal \$sqr\$ is applied to select the operation mode.

\$PP\_{generator} (A, B, i) \{\$
if \$(sqr=1)\$
else return \$PP_i\$;
}

.

 Compared with the studies in [7], [8], and [15], our model has the following four advantages: 

it is applicable to any static CMOS technology;


it is applicable to any circuit topology;


it includes the impact of circuit states;


it includes the impact of temperature variation.

